<h2 align=center>Welcome to the F Programming Language Homepage</h2>

<hr>
<center>
<p>
``Perfection is achieved, not when there is nothing more
<br>to add, but when there is nothing left to take away.'' 
<p>
- Antoine de Saint Exupery
</center>

<hr>
<center>
<p>
``I really appreciate the F software.
Usually if I can get my programs to compile under F,
they simply work.
Maybe F causes me to spend more time
analyzing my code, or forces a sharper perspective,
but it sure adds discipline to my programs.
Thanks! '' 
<p>
- Mike White
</center>

<hr>

<center>

<p>The simplest and most effective way to
use the F subset of Fortran is to use the
option -std=F with the g95 compiler.
<pre>
g95 -std=F my_program.f95
</pre>

<hr>

<p>
The g95 compiler is available at no charge from
<a href="http://www.g95.org">g95.org</a>
<br>
The g95 compiler and many useful tools can
be purchased for a modest price from the
Fortran Store.
<a href="http://www.fortran.com/compilers.html">
Click here for more information</a>.

<hr>

<p>
The syntax for F is to be found
<a href="F_bnf.html">
here</a>.

</center>

